    "1301910": {
        "Desc": "Speak with the elemental life-form",
        "Talk": [
            [
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Whew, that should be all of 'em. That wasn't too tough!"
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "Nahida, are you feeling better?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Nahida",
                    "T": "Yeah, I've calmed down now. But it doesn't seem like there's too much we can do until we receive some new leads."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Can you tell us about the Dendro Dragon? We don't know anything about it. Who is it, and what does it have to do with King Deshret?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Nahida",
                    "T": "Well, the history of dragons starts from the very beginning of Teyvat."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Nahida",
                    "T": "Sumeru was Apep's territory. In those days, the lush rainforest covered the entire nation."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Oh? So there was no desert back then?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Nahida",
                    "T": "Not at first. That came when a giant spike fell from the sky, turning a huge section of the rainforest into sand."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Nahida",
                    "T": "In an attempt to adapt to its new environment, Apep changed color from the emerald green of the forest to the yellow of the sand."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "No wonder those two elemental life-forms are always talking about the importance of \"adapting\"..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Nahida",
                    "T": "Apep has always seen itself as the master of Sumeru and has refused to recognize the new order that was established. Even now, it probably still holds great hostility toward the gods."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Nahida",
                    "T": "However, powerless against the power in the sky and then the forbidden knowledge many millennia later, it's been unable to stir up any trouble."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "I thought the gods and dragons were on good terms?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Nahida",
                    "T": "Conflicts between the two sides are destined to continue until a balance can be found."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Nahida",
                    "T": "As far as I know, Apep had been slumbering in the desert, and King Deshret had taken a great interest in it. Maybe this is why Apep was contaminated."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Nahida",
                    "T": "I'm not sure what may have led it to become involved, but rescuing it is definitely our top priority right now."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Nahida",
                    "T": "The crystal that I have in my possession is probably the key that links the two matters together."
                }
            ]
        ]
    },
